summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from Peter Reilly and Catherine Reilly, his wife, both of Seattle King County, Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated the 6th day of June, 1904, to Lots Eighteen (18), Nineteen (19) and Twenty (10) of Block Eleven (11) of Hazelwood Addition Supplemental to the City of Seattle, according to the plat thereof filled February 4th, 1888, in the office of the Auditor of said King County and recorded in Plat Book Volume 2 on Page 110 in said office to which recorded reference is hereby made and the same is made a part hereof. This property is acquired for park purposes.
